Now Greg HAS the right idea!!!!  Actually, I'd settle for plain old original
bolts as NOS fasteners have never been a requirement... heck, I've pushed to
find nice used restorable parts way more often than for nos stuff... NOS
simply means there is way more depreciation the instance you fire it up.

... I just hope all you people that will have parts this Sunday at Octo will
have the few screws and bolts that I'm still looking for...


